An Apple store in San Francisco’s Marina District was robbed twice in a week, with multiple perpetrators walking in and grabbing what they wanted. Security footage of the robberies, shown in the video below, was released by the San Francisco Police Department in an effort to find the robbers, reported Business Insider. The first robbery took place on 25 November, with the second incident taking place on 29 November. In both cases, the employees stand by and watch as hooded individuals make off with Apple products. 